legacy.full_text: As with most manifestos by killers (like the Unabomber), there is a part coherently explaining the political grievances but then when it gets to the part justifying killing people, there's nothing persuasive at all. They never have an argument for why murder will help.

This was also striking about Luigi Mangioni's manifesto. "The situation is terrible, so I did a murder". Will the murder improve the situation in any way? It doesn't even occur to them to try to answer that!
